- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with extremal graph theory, which is a subfield of discrete mathematics. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the development of a database and ecosystem of tools to assist in the study of extremal graph theory. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is another possibility as the paper uses the convex hull of graphs as points in the invariants space. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possibility as the paper uses numerical methods to obtain optimal bounds on graph invariants. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may discuss the computational complexity of obtaining extremal graphs and optimal bounds.
